Nguyen Tran Mai Thanh is an Intern Java Engineer with 0 years of commercial experience, demonstrating strong foundational knowledge in modern distributed system architectures. Their core expertise lies in designing and implementing Microservices, leveraging Domain-Driven Design (DDD), CQRS, EventSourcing, and Saga patterns. Through academic projects, Thanh has applied these concepts extensively, notably in the "Book Shop Service" where they utilized Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, and Axon Framework to build a scalable library management system, integrating Docker, Kubernetes, Apache Kafka for messaging, and Keycloak for robust authentication with OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect. This project also showcased proficiency in API Documentation with Swagger and implementing Service Discovery via Spring Cloud Netflix Eureka.
Technically, Thanh is proficient in Java, JavaScript, HTML, and CSS. They possess hands-on experience with key frameworks and libraries including Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, and React, alongside specialized tools like Axon Framework for event-driven architectures. Database skills encompass MySQL, SQL Server, and H2 Console. For DevOps and cloud-native deployments, Thanh is familiar with Docker, Kubernetes, Git, GitHub, and Apache Kafka for message queuing. Additional tools and platforms include IntelliJ IDEA, VS Code, Swagger for API documentation, Keycloak for identity management, JWT, and Spring Cloud Gateway for API routing. Thanh's academic background includes a Bachelor of Software Engineering (in progress) and B2 English proficiency.